                            <comment id="13935414" author="tripod" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 18:31:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added an additional test &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.jackrabbit.oak.security.user.UserManagerImplTest#testConcurrentCreateUser&lt;/tt&gt; in r1577651.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13935436" author="tripod" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 18:45:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the conflict is generated in &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.jackrabbit.oak.spi.state.AbstractRebaseDiff#childNodeAdded&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; childNodeAdded(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name, NodeState after) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (builder.hasChildNode(name)) {
            NodeState other = builder.child(name).getNodeState();
            addExistingNode(builder, name, other, after);
        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
            builder.setChildNode(name, after);
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO, the merge should be smart and not conflict if the 2 added nodes are identical.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13935456" author="tripod" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 19:00:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jukkaz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jukkaz&quot;&gt;jukkaz&lt;/a&gt; can you take a look at this? I don&apos;t really understand much about how merging works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13940639" author="anchela" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2014 16:33:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i tentatively added 1.0 as this is something that will for sure cause troubles.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
